commit.message: Supplementaldata has now moved to github

Only check consistency when it makes sense

Closes #74 and #73

Fix under Termux

Termux has a wrapper for getprop:

```
unset LD_LIBRARY_PATH LD_PRELOAD
PATH=$PATH:/system/bin exec /system/bin/getprop "$@"
```

I couldn't figure out how to mimic that wrapper using Python's `subprocess`.
With this fix, `tzlocal` work under Termux:

```
$ python
Python 3.6.4 (default, Jan  7 2018, 03:53:53)
[GCC 4.2.1 Compatible Android Clang 5.0.300080 ] on linux
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import tzlocal
>>> tzlocal.get_localzone()
<DstTzInfo 'Asia/Manila' LMT+8:04:00 STD>
```

commit.message:
Skip comment lines in /etc/timezone

On some systems, /etc/timezone is 2 lines, a comment, then the timezone.

Reported as a bug in Ubuntu:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/python-tzlocal/+bug/1797857

This change includes a test data and a test.
